  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Investigating the effectiveness of peer support networks in strengthening rural capacity for maternal and child healthcare in northern Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women and children in remote, arid lands of northern Kenya have very poor health and nutrition. Many women die during pregnancy and childbirth, and many children die from malnutrition or other preventable causes. Communities there, especially mobile pastoralists, have very limited access to proper state health services or trained doctors and midwives. This grant is for a community consultation about health and nutrition issues and for research into relevant interventions. They have done a similar planning exercise before for water and sanitation. The information collected will be used to design a community-led, &#x2018;peer-support&#x2019; component of a wider maternal and child health project.</narrative>
  </description>
